aspguidp.service.input.suggestion.impl

Class TemplateSuggestionService

  • java.lang.Object
    • aspguidp.service.input.suggestion.impl.TemplateSuggestionService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SuggestionService

    public class TemplateSuggestionService
extends java.lang.Object
implements SuggestionService
    Implementation of the SuggestionService interface which generates suggestions and prompt texts based on a sequence of TemplatePart instances.

    An instance of the class is initialized with a sequence of template parts. This sequence of template parts is used for the generation of suggestions and prompt texts for a given user input by the service.

    Suggestions generated by an instance of this service always suggest the value for exactly one placeholder template part. Therefore a suggestion generated by this service can be split up into 3 parts: fixed start, suggested placeholder value and fixed end.

      • TemplateSuggestionService

        public TemplateSuggestionService(java.util.List<TemplatePart> templateParts,
                                 ValidationService validationService)
        Create a new service instance for the given sequence of template parts. The given validation service is used to validate given user input.

        If a given user input is validated as invalid by the given validation service, empty suggestions and prompt texts are returned for the user input.

        Parameters:
        templateParts - sequence of template pats which is used to generate suggestions and prompt texts
        validationService - service which is used to validate given user inputs
